article_title: Two-Year U.S. Yield Rises to Four-Year High
article_text:
The yield on the two-year U.S. government debt rose to the highest level in more than four years after Federal Reserve Chairwoman Janet Yellen signaled an interest-rate increase in December is on the table.

The bond market has been under selling pressure since Oct. 28 when Fed officials signaled that they were on course to tighten monetary policy before the end of the year. Ms. Yellen reiterated the view Wednesday during her...
